title.narrative: SUPPORT FOR FAMILIES AND CAREGIVERS

description.narrative: Services that support parents and caregivers to stimulate child development and nurturing care and prevent adversity are in place and accessible to all families and caregivers, which contributes to Health And Development In Early Childhood And Adolescence, Promotion Of Care, Mental Health And Psychosocial Well-Being And Justice, Protection From Violence, Exploitation, Abuse And Neglect, Strengthening Primary Health Care And High-Impact Health Interventions, Strengthening Primary Health Care And High-Impact Health Interventions (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Evaluations, Research And Data, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: All boys and girls and families have equitable access to and utilize quality integrated social services that ensure survival and health, provision of nurturing care and protection from adversity

description.narrative: UNICEF was uniquely positioned to provide leadership, bringing together diverse partners and sectors; working comprehensively towards holistic child development – linking health, early stimulation and parenting, as well as safety, support and protection for children at risk of abandonment, or separated from their families. UNICEF has generated knowledge on early childhood intervention (ECI) services, initiated the establishment of trauma-informed healthcare as well as systemic provision of services and support to parents and caregivers through parenting programmes, helplines and applications. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:21/01/2022
